Since this is a disconnected cluster, the root cause is different.

The failure is because OLM cannot find or unpack the odf-dependencies.v4.19.12-rhodf bundle from your mirrored catalog/index image.

This line is the key symptom:

bundle unpacking failed. Reason: DeadlineExceeded

And earlier:

InstallPlan not found for CSV odf-dependencies.v4.19.12-rhodf

That usually means one of these in disconnected environments:

1. Missing mirrored bundle image


2. Missing related ODF images in mirror registry


3. CatalogSource index image incomplete


4. ICSP/ImageDigestMirrorSet issue


5. Pull secret for local registry missing


6. Catalog pod unable to pull bundle image



You already cleaned the stale 4.18 CSV conflicts correctly.

Now check the disconnected mirror side.

1. Verify CatalogSource image

Run:

oc get catalogsource -n openshift-marketplace

You should see your custom mirrored catalog, something like:

redhat-operators-disconnected

custom-operator-index

etc.


Then describe it:

oc describe catalogsource <catalogsource-name> -n openshift-marketplace

Check:

image points to local registry

pod is READY

no pull errors



---

2. Check catalog pod logs

oc get pod -n openshift-marketplace

Find the catalog pod related to your disconnected index image.

Then:

oc logs -n openshift-marketplace <catalog-pod>

Look for:

manifest unknown

unauthorized

image pull backoff

bundle not found



---

3. Verify ODF 4.19.12 bundle exists in mirror registry

From bastion:

podman login <your-local-registry>

Then:

skopeo inspect docker://<your-local-registry>/odf4/odf-operator-bundle-rhel9:v4.19.12

or whatever mirrored repo structure you use.

If this fails:

bundle image was never mirrored

or tag missing



---

4. Check IDMS / ICSP

oc get imagedigestmirrorset,imagecontentsourcepolicy

Then verify ODF registry mappings exist.


---

5. Most important check now

See if unpack job is even being created:

oc get jobs -A | grep -i unpack

and:

oc get pods -A | grep -Ei 'unpack|extract'

If none exist:

catalog resolution failing before unpack


If they exist but fail:

mirror image issue



---

6. Check package existence in catalog

Very important:

oc get packagemanifest | grep odf

You MUST see:

odf-dependencies

odf-operator


Then:

oc describe packagemanifest odf-dependencies

Verify:

stable-4.19 channel exists

currentCSV = odf-dependencies.v4.19.12-rhodf


If not: your mirrored index image does not contain ODF 4.19.12 properly.

Most likely root cause now:

incomplete/missing ODF 4.19 catalog content in disconnected mirror registry.
